_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/System_Setup_and_Configuration.md:175:Key differentiators from Pivot's current D365 environment include unified customer master eliminating HubSpot/D365 synchronization\. HubSpot integration will be further explored after go\-live to ensure alignment with Pivot’s marketing and CRM strategy\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/System_Setup_and_Configuration.md:1152:Pivot's D365 contains years of customer, vendor, employee, financial, and transaction data requiring migration to NetSuite for operational continuity and historical reporting\. Data quality varies—some duplicate customers/vendors, inconsistent naming conventions,
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/System_Setup_and_Configuration.md:1171:- Enables sales history analysis, forecasting, customer buying patterns
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/System_Setup_and_Configuration.md:1297:SharePoint connector works bidirectionally—users access SharePoint folders directly from NetSuite records \(customer, project, order, PO\), and SharePoint document libraries are searchable from within NetSuite\. Document creation triggers from NetSuite transactions—a quote created automatically creates SharePoint folder using a naming convention template \(e\.g\., "Customer Name \- Project Number \- Quote"\), and generated PDFs save directly to that folder\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/System_Setup_and_Configuration.md:1311:Quote generated saves PDF to SharePoint: "2026 Projects\\Healthcare\\St\. Mary's \- 428982\\Quotes\\Quote\-Rev1\-2026\-02\-15\.pdf\." Customer requests revisions; second quote saves "Quote\-Rev2\-2026\-02\-20\.pdf\." Both versions are accessible with revision history\.

