_Unification/working/codex-run.log:5600:Financial Management/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_FinancialManagement_v2.0.md:532:KB+Hoag currently manages banking through manual processes. Bank reconciliation requires downloading transactions from West Coast Community Bank, manually entering them into accounting records, and verifying against the GL. Credit card reconciliation is handled separately. Bill payments are prepared by the AP team (Guada/Michael), compiled into payment runs, and brought to Lorraine for approval. Once approved, payment files are manually uploaded to the bank portal for processing. Cash flow visibility requires manual Excel consolidation from multiple bank statements.
