rth solving by going to ramp.","startTime":"41:05","endTime":"41:10","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay, exactly.","startTime":"41:10","endTime":"41:11","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah, got it.","startTime":"41:11","endTime":"41:12","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I mean another kind of related headache that we may want to make note of just because we're going to.","startTime":"41:13","endTime":"41:21","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"I would like to solve for it is that typically when people are submitting expense reports that have job related costs on them, more often than not there isn't an existing line on that order to match that cost to.","startTime":"41:21","endTime":"41:36","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"It's what we have to do is once expense report is submitted, we then have to go create a line, add it to the order.","startTime":"41:36","endTime":"41:42","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"So there's Someone to job cost that.","startTime":"41:42","endTime":"41:44","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"So anyway, that's just food for thought.","startTime":"41:44","endTime":"41:47","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Is that something that we could push a line to the order and apply that cost?","startTime":"41:47","endTime":"41:53","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Because that's another part of the process.","startTime":"41:54","endTime":"41:56","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"It's manual right now.","startTime":"41:56","endTime":"41:57","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"41:58","endTime":"41:58","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Yeah, that's a good note.","startTime":"41:58","endTime":"41:59","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Great.","startTime":"42:01","endTime":"42:01","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Anything else that we should know?","startTime":"42:01","endTime":"42:04","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I mean, we'll talk a lot more when we get the final decision on which app we're using.","startTime":"42:04","endTime":"42:10","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I'm sure we'll have to have a session in the setup for that, but anything else from a high level that we should keep our eye on for expense management?","startTime":"42:10","endTime":"42:17","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I mean.","startTime":"42:26","endTime":"42:27","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"No, because I think, I mean, Expensify works great.","startTime":"42:27","endTime":"42:31","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"It works fine.","startTime":"42:31","endTime":"42:32","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"There's a whole nice structure on.","startTime":"42:32","endTime":"42:34","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"On department and what accounts, depending on what department they're in, what access to.","startTime":"42:35","endTime":"42:42","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"What accounts they have to use and post to.","startTime":"42:42","endTime":"42:44","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So we've set in the background, which works really nice.","startTime":"42:44","endTime":"42:47","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"We have good security in terms of.","startTime":"42:48","endTime":"42:51","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Approval flow in Expensify.","startTime":"42:51","endTime":"42:53","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"That works really good.","startTime":"42:53","endTime":"42:54","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And eventually everything goes through Kip anyway, so he's our gatekeeper to make sure nobody's posting stupid stuff and stuff.","startTime":"42:54","endTime":"43:02","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So.","startTime":"43:03","endTime":"43:03","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So I mean, again, Expensify works good.","startTime":"43:03","endTime":"43:06","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"It's the credit card component that we.","startTime":"43:06","endTime":"43:09","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Have to go through Expensify and then we have a manual GEO headache to go through.","startTime":"43:09","endTime":"43:14","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Expensify in itself works fine and it ends up flowing and posting into our account.","startTime":"43:14","endTime":"43:20","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So that's.","startTime":"43:20","endTime":"43:20","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"That.","startTime":"43:20","endTime":"43:21","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"That works fine.","startTime":"43:21","endTime":"43:22","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So I'm not dissing Exemptify at all.","startTime":"43:22","endTime":"43:27","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"So it's a good dream.","startTime":"43:27","endTime":"43:28","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Dream of using Expensify.","startTime":"43:29","endTime":"43:30","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Like even, like when were on site with a client and there's a Netsuite rep there and he's like, oh, yeah, don't use, don't use NetSuite expenses.","startTime":"43:31","endTime":"43:38","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Like, that's a weak point for Netsuite.","startTime":"43:38","endTime":"43:41","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Like when I come home and set aside two hours collecting all my receipts and putting them into.","startTime":"43:41","endTime":"43:46","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, I think that, I mean, that's part of.","startTime":"43:46","endTime":"43:49","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"The only thing I think that's a little clunky of Expensify is that people.","startTime":"43:49","endTime":"43:53","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Still need to take time to do their expense reports.","startTime":"43:53","endTime":"43:56","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"43:56","endTime":"43:56","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"From the demos we've seen, Ramp is.","startTime":"43:57","endTime":"44:00","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"A little bit more friendly and, you know, can take pictures with your phone and, you know, all sorts of bells and whistles.","startTime":"44:00","endTime":"44:05","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So it's a little bit more advanced, I think, than what we've seen to do with Expensify.","startTime":"44:05","endTime":"44:12","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"But, but you'll like, you'll love Ramp because I mean, literally you'll get the text from Ramp before the waiter returns with your card and to sign.","startTime":"44:13","endTime":"44:22","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"It's.","startTime":"44:23","endTime":"44:23","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"It's really nice.","startTime":"44:23","endTime":"44:24","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah, it really is.","startTime":"44:24","endTime":"44:26","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So, yeah, no, I think.","startTime":"44:26","endTime":"44:27","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"There'Ll be good benefits in there, but again, you know, we've got a lot of dueling priorities right now going on in the company, so.","startTime":"44:27","endTime":"44:35","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Yeah, for sure.","startTime":"44:35","endTime":"44:35","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"44:38","endTime":"44:38","speaker_name":"Kevin Yin","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"The next one we had was just the topic of financial security and permissions.","startTime":"44:38","endTime":"44:46","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Like who can see what at what time, what roles, can see what.","startTime":"44:46","endTime":"44:49","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So again, this might turn into another session, but the idea that like we talked about, the sales team can see commissionable GP but they can't see the project gp.","startTime":"44:50","endTime":"45:02","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Like is that a hard requirement or a preference like setting some of those things up?","startTime":"45:03","endTime":"45:08","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I think it's a preference.","startTime":"45:10","endTime":"45:11","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Because again.","startTime":"45:14","endTime":"45:15","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"We, we tried honestly, actual financial information is only the admins of Core right.","startTime":"45:15","endTime":"45:26","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Now, which are Kevin, Kip, myself, and then I think Matt and I don't even know if Mark's ever set.","startTime":"45:26","endTime":"45:34","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Up on anything, but obviously Mark doesn't use any of this, but he's, I.","startTime":"45:34","endTime":"45:37","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Think, you know, ultimately, if he ever wanted to, he can see it.","startTime":"45:37","endTime":"45:40","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"But, but I think the four.","startTime":"45:40","endTime":"45:42","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Of us have admin rights to see everything and do everything and that's the way it should be for financial data.","startTime":"45:42","endTime":"45:50","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay, got.","startTime":"45:51","endTime":"45:52","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is.","startTime":"45:54","endTime":"45:54","speaker_name":"Kevin Yin","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"I mean, it's a topic worth discussing though, because currently, I mean, the directors and account managers, they do have pretty free reign.","startTime":"45:54","endTime":"46:03","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"If it's their project, they can open it up and see line item detail and they're not really restricted from seeing anything that's related to their project.","startTime":"46:03","endTime":"46:12","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"They can't run financial statements and things like that.","startTime":"46:12","endTime":"46:15","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Right, yeah, Project data, they kind of have full access, but maybe we want to change that, I don't know.","startTime":"46:15","endTime":"46:22","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"And that's kind of how we have it set up too, is at a project level, the people assigned to that project, especially the leadership, can see that data.","startTime":"46:23","endTime":"46:31","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We would just need to be aware if there are any restrictions that we need to put in place and we have like these default permission roles and you know, as we get into implementation, we'll be kind of installing those roles into your account.","startTime":"46:31","endTime":"46:45","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We can go through and see what they can see and what they can't see.","startTime":"46:45","endTime":"46:49","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But if there are restrictions, it's like the earlier we know about that type of restriction, the better position we are to accommodate it early on.","startTime":"46:49","endTime":"46:57","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Sure.","startTime":"46:57","endTime":"46:57","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"46:58","endTime":"46:58","speaker_name":"Kevin Yin","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"46:58","endTime":"46:59","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Then there's just a couple specific ones that we need to ask questions about when setting those up.","startTime":"47:00","endTime":"47:06","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"The ability to create Journal entries.","startTime":"47:07","endTime":"47:09","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is that kind of that same group?","startTime":"47:09","endTime":"47:12","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is it even smaller than the other admin group that you mentioned?","startTime":"47:12","endTime":"47:15","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yes.","startTime":"47:16","endTime":"47:16","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"No, actually I have one more person.","startTime":"47:17","endTime":"47:19","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"To add and that's Kevin's direct report are also on the GL team.","startTime":"47:19","endTime":"47:24","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So those are the only people that can do journal entries as Celine, Kevin, myself and I don't even know if Kip can.","startTime":"47:24","endTime":"47:31","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Do you have access?","startTime":"47:31","endTime":"47:32","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"But I don't think.","startTime":"47:33","endTime":"47:33","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah, I'm an admin so I could do it.","startTime":"47:34","endTime":"47:36","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"I, I could but I, Yeah, I don't ever do them.","startTime":"47:36","endTime":"47:38","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"But yeah, admins have kind of free reign to do whatever.","startTime":"47:38","endTime":"47:41","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"47:42","endTime":"47:42","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":4},{"sentence":"In my list here I just had Lorraine, Celine and Kevin as my journal entry list.","startTime":"47:42","endTime":"47:48","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I also add Kip on there though because you know, between Kip and Kevin they're total backups for each other.","startTime":"47:49","endTime":"47:55","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"So if one can't, the other one can.","startTime":"47:55","endTime":"47:58","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So Kip should always be also included.","startTime":"47:58","endTime":"48:00","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"48:00","endTime":"48:00","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And like Kip, the role I see you playing in this, like there is need for a general netsuite administrator too.","startTime":"48:00","endTime":"48:07","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Just like the guy that has control over the account.","startTime":"48:07","endTime":"48:10","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Correct.","startTime":"48:10","endTime":"48:11","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"So it's like if you have admin assigned to you, then you pretty much have every, you know.","startTime":"48:11","endTime":"48:16","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"48:16","endTime":"48:16","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Just like everything.","startTime":"48:16","endTime":"48:17","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Yeah, exactly.","startTime":"48:18","endTime":"48:19","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay, so we'll go that way and then what about approval of payment runs?","startTime":"48:20","endTime":"48:25","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is that Lorraine only or is that Kevin and Celine as well?","startTime":"48:25","endTime":"48:30","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"No.","startTime":"48:31","endTime":"48:31","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"So the AP team puts a recommendation for me, then I go through and.","startTime":"48:31","endTime":"48:37","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"I, I then approve what we're going to pay.","startTime":"48:37","endTime":"48:41","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"I come up with a target and either then Kevin or Kip load it into the bank and then I can go in myself.","startTime":"48:42","endTime":"48:54","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Matt or Mark are the only approvers in the bank.","startTime":"48:54","endTime":"48:57","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Approvers.","startTime":"48:57","endTime":"48:58","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"48:58","endTime":"48:58","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Approvers.","startTime":"48:58","endTime":"48:59","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Yeah, in the bank.","startTime":"48:59","endTime":"49:00","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"But yes.","startTime":"49:01","endTime":"49:01","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So I at this point myself, I'm the only one to approve bank payments.","startTime":"49:01","endTime":"49:08","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"I mean got it at the bank.","startTime":"49:08","endTime":"49:11","speaker_name":"Kevin Yin","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"But like when you say approved payment runs.","startTime":"49:11","endTime":"49:13","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Chris.","startTime":"49:13","endTime":"49:14","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"What?","startTime":"49:14","endTime":"49:14","speaker_name":"Kevin Yin","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Define what you're talking about.","startTime":"49:14","endTime":"49:15","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"You're talking about within that with Orion.","startTime":"49:15","endTime":"49:19","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"And how does the payment just kind of give me high level view of what the payment process looks like?","startTime":"49:19","endTime":"49:25","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"We load AP vouchers.","startTime":"49:25","endTime":"49:26","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"The AP person then kind of with Lorraine's blessing picks and chooses what to be paid.","startTime":"49:26","endTime":"49:31","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"And then what happens from that point forward?","startTime":"49:31","endTime":"49:33","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"That's a good, that's a good question I don't know the answer to.","startTime":"49:34","endTime":"49:37","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"49:37","endTime":"49:37","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Gary or Debbie, do you know how that works in Net.","startTime":"49:38","endTime":"49:41","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"In base netsuite.","startTime":"49:41","endTime":"49:42","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I have to look at the process flow to.","startTime":"49:49","endTime":"49:51","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"I don't want to Speak out of turn.","startTime":"49:51","endTime":"49:52","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah, I mean I guess the security, the stop the security and this is the bank because somebody could.","startTime":"49:53","endTime":"49:58","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"I mean we're not printing checks.","startTime":"49:59","endTime":"50:00","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"So this is all ACH stuff.","startTime":"50:01","endTime":"50:02","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"The ACH gets file gets created, uploaded to the bank and then that's where the rubber hits the road because either Lorraine, Mark or Matt have to approve it or it goes nowhere.","startTime":"50:02","endTime":"50:13","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Yeah, that's a good point.","startTime":"50:14","endTime":"50:15","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And it is in netsuite, I think it is dealing with like the actual printing of checks.","startTime":"50:16","endTime":"50:20","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Like that's where the permission is set.","startTime":"50:20","endTime":"50:22","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So.","startTime":"50:22","endTime":"50:22","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And that's actually something we wanted to, I wanted to ask you is, you.","startTime":"50:22","endTime":"50:26","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Know, 99.9% of our payments are checks or wire.","startTime":"50:26","endTime":"50:29","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So again it's all through the bank.","startTime":"50:29","endTime":"50:31","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Every now and then we dumb state.","startTime":"50:32","endTime":"50:35","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Or something that requires a $25 check, an actual hard copy check.","startTime":"50:35","endTime":"50:39","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And that's very painful to run.","startTime":"50:39","endTime":"50:41","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And at this current state, I don't even know how to run them or I don't have the machines.","startTime":"50:42","endTime":"50:46","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Only Matt can run the checks because he actually has a check machines in his office.","startTime":"50:46","endTime":"50:52","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And usually Kip and Matt coordinate that the actual check printing because Kip does something in Core and then tells Matt what to go print.","startTime":"50:53","endTime":"51:00","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So I don't know if that's how netsuite would run.","startTime":"51:00","endTime":"51:03","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"No, I.","startTime":"51:07","endTime":"51:07","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Well, yeah, there's a couple things like connection to the actual check printing machine.","startTime":"51:07","endTime":"51:13","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Like we'd have to set up that.","startTime":"51:13","endTime":"51:14","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"That and its associated permissions.","startTime":"51:15","endTime":"51:17","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I think with NetSuite, like in check printing, the hardest thing is just getting the format of the check correct.","startTime":"51:18","endTime":"51:24","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But yeah, it's like if you could actually use one of their standard formats, you're better off than trying to do a custom template if you can.","startTime":"51:24","endTime":"51:33","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So yeah, we'd have to look at.","startTime":"51:33","endTime":"51:35","speaker_name":"Kevin Yin","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Obviously I think we should give you a copy of our stock so you.","startTime":"51:35","endTime":"51:38","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Can see it, you know.","startTime":"51:38","endTime":"51:40","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"51:40","endTime":"51:40","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And it may already be on there.","startTime":"51:40","endTime":"51:41","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"51:41","endTime":"51:42","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"51:42","endTime":"51:43","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":4},{"sentence":"Chip, is that something you can upload to the SharePoint?","startTime":"51:44","endTime":"51:46","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"51:48","endTime":"51:48","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Thank you, Lorraine.","startTime":"51:48","endTime":"51:50","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"I, I may have misheard you, but I thought I heard you say 99 of the payments are checks or wires.","startTime":"51:50","endTime":"51:58","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":4},{"sentence":"No.","startTime":"51:58","endTime":"51:58","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Ach.","startTime":"52:00","endTime":"52:00","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay, yes.","startTime":"52:00","endTime":"52:02","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"And then between those two, how much do you think is check printing?","startTime":"52:04","endTime":"52:09","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":4},{"sentence":"98%.","startTime":"52:10","endTime":"52:11","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Oh, sorry.","startTime":"52:11","endTime":"52:13","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Check printing.","startTime":"52:13","endTime":"52:13","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"No, check printing is honestly one.","startTime":"52:13","endTime":"52:16","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Every four or five months.","startTime":"52:16","endTime":"52:18","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Like we don't.","startTime":"52:18","endTime":"52:19","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay, yeah, no, we used to do some more checks when we had final.","startTime":"52:19","endTime":"52:24","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Termination, employee checks, but now we've, we're working through paylocity to get those checks cut.","startTime":"52:24","endTime":"52:30","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So that has diminished that greatly.","startTime":"52:30","endTime":"52:32","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And then now we really only write checks for those random state or agencies that require a paper check to be written.","startTime":"52:33","endTime":"52:42","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And usually, like I said, They're 25 or 50.","startTime":"52:42","endTime":"52:44","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Literally.","startTime":"52:45","endTime":"52:46","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"We had a situation where it took us forever to write a check for $10.","startTime":"52:46","endTime":"52:50","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Yeah, I'll give you $10 out of my wallet.","startTime":"52:50","endTime":"52:54","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":4},{"sentence":"No, seriously, our.","startTime":"52:54","endTime":"52:56","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Our employee Celine was like, I'll drive to the office, to the agency office and give them the cash.","startTime":"52:56","endTime":"53:02","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Like, you know, because they take the check back.","startTime":"53:02","endTime":"53:06","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Like, it was just a stupid thing.","startTime":"53:06","endTime":"53:08","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"But anyway, so, yeah, it's so random.","startTime":"53:08","endTime":"53:12","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"I can't even.","startTime":"53:12","endTime":"53:12","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Honestly, I can't even remember the last time we wrote a check right now.","startTime":"53:12","endTime":"53:15","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Probably it's been months.","startTime":"53:15","endTime":"53:17","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"53:17","endTime":"53:18","speaker_name":"Kevin Yin","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"And then maybe just to wrap that one up, if there are any permission issues that you can think of in CORE that you want to solve, we would just want to be aware of that.","startTime":"53:18","endTime":"53:28","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Anything that, like, you're like, oh, that group or that person has access in CORE and shouldn't going forward, we would just need to.","startTime":"53:28","endTime":"53:36","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"To know that you're having that issue.","startTime":"53:36","endTime":"53:38","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I think for that, I do need.","startTime":"53:38","endTime":"53:41","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"To maybe talk to Matt just a little bit.","startTime":"53:41","endTime":"53:43","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"53:43","endTime":"53:43","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"I can speak again to the finance.","startTime":"53:43","endTime":"53:45","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Side, which we're hopeful that only those people listed have access to the finance.","startTime":"53:45","endTime":"53:51","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And obviously I need my AP team to have AP and AR W. But other than that, nobody else should have financial access.","startTime":"53:51","endTime":"53:59","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And then I do need to talk to Matt, though, about his, like, the operational side, like what we talked about, you know, that people can see on their.","startTime":"54:00","endTime":"54:10","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"On their side.","startTime":"54:10","endTime":"54:10","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"54:11","endTime":"54:12","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"I mean, I know one thing that's been historically been a struggle with CORE is kind of the org charter hierarchy.","startTime":"54:12","endTime":"54:18","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Like, I'd want a supervisor to be built to see her.","startTime":"54:18","endTime":"54:22","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"His or her jobs and then.","startTime":"54:22","endTime":"54:25","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"And also the jobs of anyone who reports to that person.","startTime":"54:25","endTime":"54:28","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"And then we need the tree built out like that.","startTime":"54:28","endTime":"54:31","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"And it's.","startTime":"54:31","endTime":"54:31","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"It's never been very clear in core.","startTime":"54:31","endTime":"54:34","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Very easy to do.","startTime":"54:34","endTime":"54:35","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"It's a very flat structure.","startTime":"54:36","endTime":"54:37","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"We're not a flat company.","startTime":"54:37","endTime":"54:38","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"We have a lot of layers.","startTime":"54:38","endTime":"54:39","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"54:40","endTime":"54:40","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"So that's the permission I could think of.","startTime":"54:40","endTime":"54:43","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"We want people to see their stuff and the people who report to them and then not any different teams that don't have anything to do with them.","startTime":"54:43","endTime":"54:51","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Yeah, there's a lot of leeway for that.","startTime":"54:51","endTime":"54:55","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"In netsuite, it's pretty easy to set up.","startTime":"54:55","endTime":"54:57","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You're essentially just.","startTime":"54:57","endTime":"54:58","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You're like assigning supervisors and you can stack supervisors and everything.","startTime":"54:58","endTime":"55:02","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And that's actually what drives a lot of the approval Process as well.","startTime":"55:02","endTime":"55:05","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And then for a lot of fields in netsuite, especially assignment fields, they have this concept of like instead of giving a list of every name in the company, you can select.","startTime":"55:06","endTime":"55:18","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Like I want to see either just mine or I want to see mine and my teams or mine and my employees.","startTime":"55:18","endTime":"55:25","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And that's a single thing that you would select and it would show everything there.","startTime":"55:25","endTime":"55:28","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Nice.","startTime":"55:29","endTime":"55:29","speaker_name":"Kevin Yin","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, that'll be helpful.","startTime":"55:30","endTime":"55:31","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Okay, we got two, we got five minutes and two topics.","startTime":"55:32","endTime":"55:36","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And I'm sure that these are going to be bigger discussions, but talk a little bit about fixed asset management.","startTime":"55:36","endTime":"55:41","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"If I'm not mistaken, you guys are using Bloomberg for that.","startTime":"55:41","endTime":"55:47","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So I think we came down to like it being around and I don't know if this is before or after discount, but it being around $4,000 a year for NetSuite's fixed asset module.","startTime":"55:49","endTime":"56:02","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I'm sorry, how much?","startTime":"56:02","endTime":"56:03","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Fourth, it's listed here as $4,000.","startTime":"56:04","endTime":"56:06","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I just want to get an actual quote on that because I don't know if that's before or after discount.","startTime":"56:06","endTime":"56:11","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So it's per year.","startTime":"56:11","endTime":"56:12","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay, so 4,000 per year.","startTime":"56:12","endTime":"56:14","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"56:14","endTime":"56:14","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"56:14","endTime":"56:15","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is that something that I'd like to see because again, the capabilities of it, again being all in netsuite might beneficial for us then to continue in Bloomberg.","startTime":"56:16","endTime":"56:26","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"So I'd love to see that and then we can make an informed decision.","startTime":"56:26","endTime":"56:32","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"56:32","endTime":"56:33","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"What are the, what are the critical aspects of Bloomberg that the fixed asset module would have to have in order to make it like a one to.","startTime":"56:33","endTime":"56:41","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"One or better for me?","startTime":"56:41","endTime":"56:43","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Again, obviously the book stuff, you know, but really it's the tax component, the tax depreciation, the tax things, because those are very specific reports we have to run for our auditors.","startTime":"56:43","endTime":"56:54","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay, all right, that's good to know.","startTime":"56:55","endTime":"56:57","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"56:57","endTime":"56:57","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So Debbie will look for whatever it is, videos, documents, or a demo of the fixed asset module.","startTime":"56:57","endTime":"57:06","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"57:06","endTime":"57:07","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Okay, give me one second.","startTime":"57:07","endTime":"57:10","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Kevin.","startTime":"57:10","endTime":"57:10","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Is that where we know in lease crunch is where we do the operating leases to capital leases?","startTime":"57:10","endTime":"57:15","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Is that where it does the evaluation?","startTime":"57:15","endTime":"57:17","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay, so that's something else we need to talk about because I don't know if then this netSuite module, does that the leases in there or is.","startTime":"57:17","endTime":"57:26","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"There a, is there a separate module for that?","startTime":"57:26","endTime":"57:30","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Well, there's like some leasing management built into NetSuite.","startTime":"57:30","endTime":"57:35","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I have to look at what actually.","startTime":"57:35","endTime":"57:36","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"It does and if it applies to this.","startTime":"57:36","endTime":"57:38","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But I know that there is ability to manage some of that.","startTime":"57:38","endTime":"57:41","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But.","startTime":"57:41","endTime":"57:41","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, so with fixed assets, you get their lease component.","startTime":"57:41","endTime":"57:46","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"I Would say if you're used to something like Lease query or a little bit more sophisticated, yeah, netsuite's probably not going to meet your requirements.","startTime":"57:46","endTime":"57:54","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"You're going to want to stay with least query.","startTime":"57:54","endTime":"57:55","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"But we can look at it.","startTime":"57:55","endTime":"57:56","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"But it does, it is part of the fixed asset module.","startTime":"57:56","endTime":"57:59","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"58:00","endTime":"58:00","speaker_name":"Kevin Yin","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So, okay, that's something we need to.","startTime":"58:01","endTime":"58:03","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Definitely look at because obviously the capability.","startTime":"58:03","endTime":"58:05","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Of dropping in the key metrics and.","startTime":"58:05","endTime":"58:08","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Then it coming back and saying, oh.","startTime":"58:08","endTime":"58:10","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"No, this is an operating lease.","startTime":"58:10","endTime":"58:11","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Or it's, you know, are you using.","startTime":"58:11","endTime":"58:14","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Lease query or anything like that now?","startTime":"58:14","endTime":"58:15","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Or is that all.","startTime":"58:15","endTime":"58:16","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"It's called lease crunch.","startTime":"58:16","endTime":"58:17","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"It's lease crunch.","startTime":"58:17","endTime":"58:19","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"58:19","endTime":"58:19","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"58:19","endTime":"58:19","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"58:19","endTime":"58:20","speaker_name":"Gary Strickland","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And that also does all of the.","startTime":"58:20","endTime":"58:23","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"ASC842 reporting, which is the ROU stuff.","startTime":"58:23","endTime":"58:27","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So again, it's very accounting backbone steadfast.","startTime":"58:27","endTime":"58:32","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So we definitely need that.","startTime":"58:32","endTime":"58:34","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So I don't know.","startTime":"58:34","endTime":"58:35","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Again, I don't know if we keep Lease Crunch or we can go to netsuite.","startTime":"58:35","endTime":"58:38","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay, okay.","startTime":"58:39","endTime":"58:41","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"And then the last one, probably get into this more in kind of the business intelligence stuff, but through my transcripts, like it pulled out a quote that just says, lorraine uses backlog forecasting.","startTime":"58:41","endTime":"58:57","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So when we talk about budget and forecasting, like what does that look like?","startTime":"58:58","endTime":"59:02","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is it a spreadsheet, is it a report in Core?","startTime":"59:02","endTime":"59:06","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"There's some parameters around that.","startTime":"59:08","endTime":"59:09","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"The backlog is everything that's in the queue and it's in Core and Kevin or Kip, pull out the report and.","startTime":"59:10","endTime":"59:20","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Tell us what, you know, what we're expected to bill in the upcoming months according to that backlog.","startTime":"59:20","endTime":"59:27","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So based on orders that are in there that have been flipped when we're going to be able to build them.","startTime":"59:27","endTime":"59:32","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So that's in Core, but 100% the.","startTime":"59:34","endTime":"59:39","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Budgeting and then the actual forecast is 100% done in Excel and done by me.","startTime":"59:39","endTime":"59:44","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"59:45","endTime":"59:45","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So there's, there are modules for that in netsuite.","startTime":"59:46","endTime":"59:49","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We would just need to maybe have a session.","startTime":"59:49","endTime":"59:53","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We might need to just have a session on what are the needs and what is like the future desire for how deep you want to go with that.","startTime":"59:54","endTime":"01:00:04","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Like, you know, can we run simple reports for that in netsuite or do you actually need like the budget.","startTime":"01:00:04","endTime":"01:00:12","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Budget and planning module in NetSuite.","startTime":"01:00:12","endTime":"01:00:15","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So right now I'm going to say we do not.","startTime":"01:00:16","endTime":"01:00:19","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"We are not an organization that does budgeting and tracks budgets by department or anything like that.","startTime":"01:00:19","endTime":"01:00:27","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Nobody is inputting expenses and planning their expenses stuff.","startTime":"01:00:27","endTime":"01:00:30","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"I, I do it again at a very high level on Excel.","startTime":"01:00:31","endTime":"01:00:34","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"I talk to my GMs, they tell me kind of their events and expenditure and stuff.","startTime":"01:00:34","endTime":"01:00:39","speaker