e":"27:39","endTime":"27:42","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Where are they capturing their initial scope?","startTime":"27:42","endTime":"27:45","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So, Kim, I think it basically might be in the marketing request or the design request is the initial scope.","startTime":"27:46","endTime":"27:52","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Depends.","startTime":"27:52","endTime":"27:52","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So if it's a bid, that initial scope's going through the marketing request and the design request.","startTime":"27:52","endTime":"27:57","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"If it's a non bid, then that initial scope's getting captured in the design request.","startTime":"27:57","endTime":"28:01","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Got it.","startTime":"28:04","endTime":"28:04","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It's usually not getting captured in this.","startTime":"28:04","endTime":"28:06","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"In Zendesk, because Zendesk is only capturing project date and timeline and amount.","startTime":"28:06","endTime":"28:14","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So it's not really happening on the CRM.","startTime":"28:14","endTime":"28:16","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"It could happen like again, it goes.","startTime":"28:16","endTime":"28:19","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Back to how much do you want to copy and paste.","startTime":"28:19","endTime":"28:21","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So, like, people aren't going to put everything in Zendesk, then put everything in the request and then put everything in Core and so on, because they're just having to copy everything.","startTime":"28:21","endTime":"28:30","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So I could see it flowing.","startTime":"28:30","endTime":"28:32","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"If that same information just keeps pulling all the way through as you go, you only have to put the address in once because that's the site address and it's going to show up on the quote and so on and so on.","startTime":"28:32","endTime":"28:42","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, so the scope can get.","startTime":"28:42","endTime":"28:44","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"If we capture the scope at the opportunity, and then that opportunity initiates the marketing request, the design request, the PM requests, the labor request, then great, they're all getting the same scope.","startTime":"28:45","endTime":"28:58","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"We know that they're getting the same information.","startTime":"28:58","endTime":"28:59","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, yeah, that's exactly how it'll work.","startTime":"29:00","endTime":"29:02","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So you only have to put that information in once.","startTime":"29:02","endTime":"29:04","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Now, the one thing to consider is because it kind of works in that linear fashion, if I'm working on my opportunity and I put in my scope, then that flows to the labor quote, that flows to the design request or whatever.","startTime":"29:04","endTime":"29:16","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"If somebody starts adding scope on any of those other documents, there's no way for that to retroactively update the Opportunity scope field.","startTime":"29:16","endTime":"29:25","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So one thing to consider is where is kind of like the where would be the most important place for that source of truth on scope to be.","startTime":"29:26","endTime":"29:35","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Where should that be captured?","startTime":"29:36","endTime":"29:37","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Now, there are things that we can do to make sure those fields stay in sync that can sometimes get a little tricky.","startTime":"29:38","endTime":"29:44","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We just have to think about some.","startTime":"29:48","endTime":"29:49","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Of the places that people can mess.","startTime":"29:49","endTime":"29:52","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It up a little bit.","startTime":"29:52","endTime":"29:53","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So when something goes from an opportunity to a project, does that matter?","startTime":"29:55","endTime":"30:00","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Like, do you GSI go back to then the opportunity to revise the scope as the project evolves?","startTime":"30:00","endTime":"30:06","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah, because the project, in our system, the project is really almost kind of just a reporting tool.","startTime":"30:07","endTime":"30:11","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You're not actually even doing much activity on the project except reporting.","startTime":"30:11","endTime":"30:16","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Looking at KPIs, it aggregates all the tasks, all the messages, and everything across all the transactions that are associated with the project.","startTime":"30:16","endTime":"30:25","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But you're not typically initiating anything from the project.","startTime":"30:25","endTime":"30:28","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It's kind of like this container and it aggregates all the information there for reporting purposes.","startTime":"30:30","endTime":"30:36","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So I have to remove the definition of opportunity as like pie in the sky.","startTime":"30:38","endTime":"30:45","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"And it's really more.","startTime":"30:45","endTime":"30:47","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"It's an act.","startTime":"30:47","endTime":"30:48","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"It could be an active project as well.","startTime":"30:48","endTime":"30:50","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yes.","startTime":"30:51","endTime":"30:51","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, yeah.","startTime":"30:51","endTime":"30:52","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Like, as soon as you create an opportunity, we automatically create that project record.","startTime":"30:52","endTime":"30:56","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So if you start tracking time against the opportunity or expense reports because you know they're doing sales activities, all that, those costs can start getting aggregated to the project at that point.","startTime":"30:57","endTime":"31:07","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So you will have a lot of these projects that have very little data.","startTime":"31:07","endTime":"31:11","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And that's not really a problem.","startTime":"31:12","endTime":"31:13","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And the idea, the reason why we did that, the idea is we wanted to be able to give you reporting on.","startTime":"31:15","endTime":"31:21","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Here's all the projects you didn't win, and here's all the costs associated with.","startTime":"31:21","endTime":"31:24","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Those projects that you didn't win.","startTime":"31:24","endTime":"31:25","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And then you could filter all that by sales rep or.","startTime":"31:26","endTime":"31:30","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I mean, I'm not trying to like.","startTime":"31:31","endTime":"31:33","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Be the bad guy.","startTime":"31:34","endTime":"31:35","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We look at it now, so it's not okay.","startTime":"31:35","endTime":"31:37","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, just not as easy to look up.","startTime":"31:37","endTime":"31:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So.","startTime":"31:40","endTime":"31:40","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"So I think for me, if, like, if we're Going to have to relearn then.","startTime":"31:40","endTime":"31:45","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"31:46","endTime":"31:46","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Opportunity is no longer like the opportunity of it just being a lead.","startTime":"31:46","endTime":"31:52","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"It's.","startTime":"31:52","endTime":"31:52","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"The opportunity is where all the information lives.","startTime":"31:52","endTime":"31:55","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So if the scope changes, we have to go update the opportunity to show that new scope.","startTime":"31:55","endTime":"32:00","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"But therefore, if we update the opportunity.","startTime":"32:00","endTime":"32:02","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"We would need the opportunity to push.","startTime":"32:02","endTime":"32:03","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"That update to everything else that's already out there existing.","startTime":"32:03","endTime":"32:06","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"32:09","endTime":"32:09","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So that is something that we can do if we want to.","startTime":"32:09","endTime":"32:11","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"If you want to say the opportunity is kind of the single source of truth for scope, then we can make sure that those records stay in sync.","startTime":"32:11","endTime":"32:19","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"The other reason why I like that idea, Matt, is because, and I think we talked about this before, on the CRM side, you have one opportunity and you could have three quotes tied to that one opportunity because maybe you're giving them good, better, best, or three different options or whatever.","startTime":"32:19","endTime":"32:35","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Or you iterate it or whatever.","startTime":"32:35","endTime":"32:37","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So when you do your pipeline, they.","startTime":"32:37","endTime":"32:38","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Can'T make a decision in time.","startTime":"32:38","endTime":"32:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So we have to split orders.","startTime":"32:40","endTime":"32:41","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, right.","startTime":"32:41","endTime":"32:43","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But your pipeline report is.","startTime":"32:44","endTime":"32:46","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is going to be fed by your opportunity.","startTime":"32:46","endTime":"32:48","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So now the question is, well, what.","startTime":"32:49","endTime":"32:50","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"What's the dollar amount on that opportunity?","startTime":"32:50","endTime":"32:52","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Because that's what's feeding my pipeline.","startTime":"32:52","endTime":"32:53","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I have three quotes out here, and maybe they're 1 million, 2 million, and 3 million.","startTime":"32:53","endTime":"32:57","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So which.","startTime":"32:57","endTime":"32:58","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Which number should feed my pipeline?","startTime":"32:58","endTime":"33:00","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"33:00","endTime":"33:00","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So somebody needs to kind of manage that dollar amount on the opportunity to make sure that the product pipeline report is somewhat accurate.","startTime":"33:00","endTime":"33:06","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So if we're making the opportunity kind of that source of truth for the dollar amount for pipeline and for scope, and maybe there's some other opportunities there, we can train the team just to make sure that, like, hey, here's.","startTime":"33:07","endTime":"33:21","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"In the sales meeting, we look at the opportunity and here are the things that we're updating.","startTime":"33:21","endTime":"33:24","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We're updating our expected close date or booking date, our dollar amount, because that's feeding our pipeline.","startTime":"33:24","endTime":"33:31","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And.","startTime":"33:31","endTime":"33:31","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":4},{"sentence":"And our scope.","startTime":"33:31","endTime":"33:32","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Has our scope changed?","startTime":"33:32","endTime":"33:34","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Has it updated?","startTime":"33:34","endTime":"33:34","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"33:35","endTime":"33:36","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"I guess on that then is like, when do we stop touching the opportunity?","startTime":"33:36","endTime":"33:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So, like, how does the opportunity stop showing up in the pipeline when it goes to.","startTime":"33:40","endTime":"33:44","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Is it when the quote becomes an order?","startTime":"33:45","endTime":"33:46","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"33:47","endTime":"33:47","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"33:48","endTime":"33:48","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Because, you know, there's also going to be a point where, like, I don't expect people, you know, if Kimmy goes out to a job, goes to an OAC meeting, and in that OAC meeting, they're like, hey, we want to go from, you know, the mother's room chair.","startTime":"33:48","endTime":"34:02","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"We want this instead of that.","startTime":"34:02","endTime":"34:04","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"I don't expect Kimmy to go Back into the opportunity, type in the new mothers.","startTime":"34:04","endTime":"34:07","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Like, she's going to walk over to Rafina and be like, rafina, I need you to change this.","startTime":"34:07","endTime":"34:11","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Like, yeah, so I don't want it to become, you know, this task oriented organization of like, oh, we've got to go back and update the scope and.","startTime":"34:11","endTime":"34:22","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Then like, no, just get it, get shit done.","startTime":"34:22","endTime":"34:25","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"That's the goal.","startTime":"34:25","endTime":"34:26","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So whatever that takes.","startTime":"34:26","endTime":"34:27","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, yeah.","startTime":"34:27","endTime":"34:28","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Don't overdo it.","startTime":"34:28","endTime":"34:29","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Thank you.","startTime":"34:29","endTime":"34:30","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah, yeah.","startTime":"34:30","endTime":"34:31","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"There's one other thing you could do too, Matt, and not to give you too many options.","startTime":"34:31","endTime":"34:34","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You know, natively netsuite.","startTime":"34:35","endTime":"34:36","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"When you take that quote, you convert it to a sales order, it's booked and the opportunity is automatically changed to closed one.","startTime":"34:36","endTime":"34:43","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"The quote is automatically changed to closed one.","startTime":"34:43","endTime":"34:45","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And now you're working with the sales order from that point on.","startTime":"34:45","endTime":"34:48","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"34:49","endTime":"34:49","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You could lock in the.","startTime":"34:49","endTime":"34:52","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Like if you went to, let's just say you had three quotes and you changed one of those quotes to a status like in negotiation and your probability for that is 95%.","startTime":"34:52","endTime":"35:03","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You could at that point then say, okay, well we're not considering the other two quotes anymore.","startTime":"35:03","endTime":"35:08","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"This is the only quote that we're considering because it's moved to this particular status.","startTime":"35:08","endTime":"35:11","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So you could have that option as well.","startTime":"35:12","endTime":"35:14","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And then once it hits the status, it automatically updates the amount, the dollar amount on the opportunity.","startTime":"35:14","endTime":"35:20","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So there are, there is some room there for automation if we just carefully think through when precisely that should happen.","startTime":"35:21","endTime":"35:27","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"35:28","endTime":"35:28","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"35:29","endTime":"35:29","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"I mean we don't Normally issue like three quotes.","startTime":"35:30","endTime":"35:32","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"We'll issue three ROMs, but we're not going to issue three quotes.","startTime":"35:32","endTime":"35:35","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So if they need a good best, we're going to do that outside the system because it's just faster and easier and it's less clutter in the end.","startTime":"35:35","endTime":"35:43","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Usually it's if we create a quote.","startTime":"35:44","endTime":"35:47","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"What'S going to happen?","startTime":"35:48","endTime":"35:49","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Move forward as an order, I mean, or we'll void the quote or cancel the quote, but.","startTime":"35:49","endTime":"35:54","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"35:55","endTime":"35:55","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We don't normally issue three proposals for three different things.","startTime":"35:55","endTime":"35:59","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"We just say, what do you want?","startTime":"35:59","endTime":"36:01","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"We're not going to go and create a proposal until we know what you want.","startTime":"36:01","endTime":"36:03","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, got it.","startTime":"36:05","endTime":"36:06","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay, Very good.","startTime":"36:06","endTime":"36:07","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah, I'm.","startTime":"36:08","endTime":"36:10","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So much of what we do happens in Google Slides before we ever even get to a quote because we're getting them to sign off on that Google Slide deck before we start to build out a spec.","startTime":"36:15","endTime":"36:25","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"And then when we build out that spec, we're loading that spec into core and then that's what's issuing our proposal.","startTime":"36:25","endTime":"36:31","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So literally the proposal is like the very last thing we do before we place the order.","startTime":"36:31","endTime":"36:36","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So everything that's getting like forecasted before that is just a rounded up number?","startTime":"36:39","endTime":"36:45","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Well, I don't know.","startTime":"36:45","endTime":"36:46","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"We do have a few AMs that like to put into the penny what their ROM says, but usually it's a round enough number to clears to the closest thousandth and that's what we're forecasting.","startTime":"36:46","endTime":"36:56","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So.","startTime":"36:56","endTime":"36:56","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay, I don't know that we'll run into that.","startTime":"36:57","endTime":"36:59","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So we might be able to just build it out to say whatever is.","startTime":"36:59","endTime":"37:02","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"You know what we do right now.","startTime":"37:03","endTime":"37:06","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"The report we pull is as forecast as versus actual.","startTime":"37:06","endTime":"37:09","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So what was forecasted and then what was the actual amount that was booked and was there a difference greater or lower?","startTime":"37:10","endTime":"37:15","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So then we look at that every month to see forecasting accuracy.","startTime":"37:15","endTime":"37:19","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Gotcha.","startTime":"37:20","endTime":"37:21","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"37:21","endTime":"37:22","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Is there.","startTime":"37:25","endTime":"37:25","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So with.","startTime":"37:26","endTime":"37:26","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"In light of the fact that you, long story short, don't build anything special for it because I think we're fine with just the way it is.","startTime":"37:26","endTime":"37:32","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"37:32","endTime":"37:33","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"37:33","endTime":"37:33","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Well, so my next question was, is there anything, since you're doing so much before the quoting and outside of the system, is there anything that the system, the new system can do to help support any of that?","startTime":"37:33","endTime":"37:44","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, I think that, well, I mean one you talked about like if we get all those requests into the opportunity and not have to like go open a quote just for those requests and that's super helpful, whatever we can do or create a field or however that works so that we can link that work that they're doing outside the system back to that opportunity so that if I go look at that opportunity and I want to go see what that, where they're at in that process of the Google Docs, I can click a link.","startTime":"37:45","endTime":"38:15","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"I know obviously we're going to have to go and paste that link.","startTime":"38:15","endTime":"38:17","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"It's not like it's going to go auto find it, but I want to be able to just go direct from the opportunity and click a link and it take me to where that work is being done so I can see where it's at in progress.","startTime":"38:17","endTime":"38:27","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"That would be super helpful.","startTime":"38:29","endTime":"38:30","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Kimmy, any other thoughts?","startTime":"38:30","endTime":"38:31","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Well, this is where I imagine and presumably there is that resource management component where as opportunities need to be assigned those different resources, we're able to see what's on a current resources plate to be able to see what would be a good match for the things that aren't yet assigned.","startTime":"38:33","endTime":"38:52","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah, yeah, definitely.","startTime":"38:52","endTime":"38:54","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"38:54","endTime":"38:55","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Right at the opportunity level you have the order team assignment utility where you can assign resources to the at that point you're assigning it to the opportunity which will eventually become the order.","startTime":"38:55","endTime":"39:05","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But you're able to do it as early as the opportunity.","startTime":"39:06","endTime":"39:09","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You could do it at the quote or the sales order, but as early as the opportunity.","startTime":"39:09","endTime":"39:13","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And then you'll have dashboards where you could see everybody and what they're assigned to and counts of how many orders are assigned to or projects are assigned to and things like that.","startTime":"39:14","endTime":"39:23","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Then the other thing I was thinking about that I think is potentially tangentially related, but not directly is I know that there's our Google Drive and that there's our, the SharePoint and then there's the whole NetSuite file cabinet, for lack of a better word.","startTime":"39:25","endTime":"39:41","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"39:41","endTime":"39:41","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And I know early on we had talked about how we would definitely have some things in NetSuite, which I imagine basically as our whole order processing folder.","startTime":"39:41","endTime":"39:51","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"But when you ask the question about what could we be doing like pre quote that might be helpful?","startTime":"39:52","endTime":"39:57","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Like I don't know to what extent the, those presentations, the drawings, the budget specs.","startTime":"39:57","endTime":"40:07","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Right now I imagine those things living in drive because they're not directly associated with an actual order, but a pre order.","startTime":"40:08","endTime":"40:15","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Like does it, what makes sense, does it all make sense to go into each location so that we're really clear to users about what gets saved where so people can find it when they need it for historical and our matching purposes?","startTime":"40:16","endTime":"40:33","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"40:33","endTime":"40:33","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"40:34","endTime":"40:35","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So no, that's a really good point to bring up.","startTime":"40:35","endTime":"40:38","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So SharePoint, the SharePoint integration does allow you to drag and drop files right onto the NetSuite record.","startTime":"40:38","endTime":"40:45","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So let's just say at the opportunity level, or maybe it's at the labor quote or it's at the design request, but you can drag and drop a file right there onto that record in NetSuite and it saves it to SharePoint.","startTime":"40:46","endTime":"40:57","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But when you're in NetSuite, it looks like it's attached to that record.","startTime":"40:57","endTime":"41:00","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So the user's not in SharePoint.","startTime":"41:01","endTime":"41:04","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"That's where it's backend cloud server.","startTime":"41:04","endTime":"41:07","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So everything lives in netsuite.","startTime":"41:08","endTime":"41:10","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, everything lives in netsuite in that sense.","startTime":"41:10","endTime":"41:12","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And there is a folder structure that we have a folder structure paradigm that will work with you on that looks pretty much like how most dealers are doing it in either SharePoint or Drive Now.","startTime":"41:12","endTime":"41:23","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Oh, well, you know.","startTime":"41:24","endTime":"41:24","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yours.","startTime":"41:27","endTime":"41:27","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"41:27","endTime":"41:28","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Six month process of a drive system that I would love to just put through the shredder.","startTime":"41:28","endTime":"41:33","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So we'll see yours, Marcos, we'd be interested.","startTime":"41:33","endTime":"41:35","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"41:35","endTime":"41:36","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"41:36","endTime":"41:37","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So maybe an action item for Chris to get with Tyler and we'll get the SharePoint folder structure proposal ready for them to review that as well.","startTime":"41:38","endTime":"41:48","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But.","startTime":"41:48","endTime":"41:49","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And Lorraine, I'm hoping to not have like a bunch of like, oh, all the POs have to get exported and put into this.","startTime":"41:51","endTime":"41:59","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Like, I just want everything to live in the system, not the way we're doing it today, so.","startTime":"41:59","endTime":"42:04","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"42:04","endTime":"42:04","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah, exactly.","startTime":"42:04","endTime":"42:06","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"42:06","endTime":"42:06","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"You got two enthusiastic thumbs up over there.","startTime":"42:08","endTime":"42:10","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"We're paying a lot of people to drag things around into different places.","startTime":"42:11","endTime":"42:15","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"42:15","endTime":"42:15","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And duplicate efforts.","startTime":"42:15","endTime":"42:16","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"It's stupid.","startTime":"42:16","endTime":"42:17","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah, yeah.","startTime":"42:17","endTime":"42:18","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"The majority of the stuff will automatically go into SharePoint inside of NetSuite, there's a few things that we're GSI working on.","startTime":"42:18","endTime":"42:24","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Like I think like the PDF composer saves to the NetSuite file cabinet.","startTime":"42:25","endTime":"42:28","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Can you use the exact term?","startTime":"42:28","endTime":"42:30","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It's called file Cabinet netsuite.","startTime":"42:30","endTime":"42:31","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So there's a few things that GSI get saved in NetSuite file cabinet, but we're gonna be moving them to the SharePoint folder as well.","startTime":"42:33","endTime":"42:39","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So.","startTime":"42:40","endTime":"42:41","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"42:41","endTime":"42:41","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"The idea though is that everything created inside NetSuite goes into SharePoint and it, but it's accessible right there from NetSuite, so you'll have that.","startTime":"42:41","endTime":"42:50","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Really.","startTime":"42:51","endTime":"42:51","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"I think the only thing that's going.","startTime":"42:51","endTime":"42:52","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"To live outside that is going to be any docs that end up getting created, most likely the Lookbook and then any CET files.","startTime":"42:52","endTime":"43:01","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So more of the visual stuff, but less of the what we're seeing right now as far as the.","startTime":"43:02","endTime":"43:08","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"What we're producing in core and exporting and putting into drive.","startTime":"43:09","endTime":"43:12","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, yeah.","startTime":"43:12","endTime":"43:13","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And I will say the way that dealers are doing this is they're using SharePoint inside of NetSuite, but then they're also navigating SharePoint that same folder structure, because that's what they're accustomed to.","startTime":"43:13","endTime":"43:22","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And they are dropping their CT files and everything else in there.","startTime":"43:22","endTime":"43:25","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So you can access that from either the SharePoint user interface or from the NetSuite user interface, so you don't have to have this split.","startTime":"43:25","endTime":"43:34","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And, and you know, netsuite's dropping the files here, but you're putting your other files over here somewhere.","startTime":"43:34","endTime":"43:39","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It can all be the same place.","startTime":"43:39","endTime":"43:41","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"In my brain though.","startTime":"43:42","endTime":"43:43","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"That just sounds like a third place.","startTime":"43:43","endTime":"43:44","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Like.","startTime":"43:46","endTime":"43:46","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"43:47","endTime":"43:48","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Do you have an on premise server right now?","startTime":"43:49","endTime":"43:51","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"No.","startTime":"43:52","endTime":"43:52","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"43:52","endTime":"43:53","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So everything's cloud based.","startTime":"43:53","endTime":"43:54","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I mean, we do, but they're really just over engineered print servers.","startTime":"43:54","endTime":"43:58","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"That's all they do.","startTime":"43:58","endTime":"43:59","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"43:59","endTime":"44:00","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"They allow you to connect the Internet and they allow you to print but there's no files stored on any of that.","startTime":"44:00","endTime":"44:04","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay, good.","startTime":"44:04","endTime":"44:05","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"44:05","endTime":"44:06","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So everything is stored in Google Drive at this point.","startTime":"44:06","endTime":"44:08","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"But one thing that we're facing and we'll talk about is we're running out of room on Google Drive because Google Drive has a very hard limit on not size, but of items.","startTime":"44:08","endTime":"44:19","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"And it counts every folder, accounts, every text document, every copy, it counts everything.","startTime":"44:20","endTime":"44:26","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"And so then we have to keep expanding these drives to archive and so on and so on.","startTime":"44:26","endTime":"44:31","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So this will reduce the amount of this being pushed there, but we'll decide as an internal team what lives in Drive and then what lives in SharePoint, aka NetSuite.","startTime":"44:31","endTime":"44:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, very good.","startTime":"44:41","endTime":"44:42","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"A couple more questions about requests.","startTime":"44:44","endTime":"44:46","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So design requests.","startTime":"44:46","endTime":"44:47","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is that the salesperson that's triggering that as well?","startTime":"44:49","endTime":"44:51","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Sales or account management?","startTime":"44:52","endTime":"44:53","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"44:54","endTime":"44:54","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Great.","startTime":"44:54","endTime":"44:55","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And then how are the designers are assigned?","startTime":"44:56","endTime":"44:58","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is that like.","startTime":"44:58","endTime":"44:59","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Does the request initially go to a manager?","startTime":"44:59","endTime":"45:01","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Then the manager assigns it.","startTime":"45:01","endTime":"45:02","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Perfect.","startTime":"45:02","endTime":"45:03","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And then after that it gets handed off to.","startTime":"45:06","endTime":"45:08","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Oh, yeah.","startTime":"45:11","endTime":"45:11","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"How did.","startTime":"45:11","endTime":"45:12","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So how.","startTime":"45:12","endTime":"45:12","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Where does the.","startTime":"45:12","endTime":"45:13","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"How does the.","startTime":"45:13","endTime":"45:13","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Where's.","startTime":"45:13","endTime":"45:14","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"What's the intersection of design requests and labor quote requests?","startTime":"45:14","endTime":"45:17","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"What does that look like in your organization?","startTime":"45:17","endTime":"45:19","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"There is none.","startTime":"45:20","endTime":"45:21","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"45:22","endTime":"45:22","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"You're typically doing the design work first.","startTime":"45:24","endTime":"45:26","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It depends.","startTime":"45:28","endTime":"45:28","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"45:29","endTime":"45:30","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Not always.","startTime":"45:30","endTime":"45:31","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah, they don't.","startTime":"45:31","endTime":"45:32","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"45:32","endTime":"45:33","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Sometimes simultaneously.","startTime":"45:34","endTime":"45:36","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Sometimes we get, you know, we're putting in a design request and a labor request at the exact same time.","startTime":"45:36","endTime":"45:42","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay, yeah.","startTime":"45:42","endTime":"45:43","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"This depends.","startTime":"45:43","endTime":"45:44","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"But again, it'd be nice if in.","startTime":"45:44","endTime":"45:47","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"The opportunity, you know, you're putting in scope, you're putting in location, you're putting all that stuff in so that really, when you hit a request, it's just transferring what's already in there to the next person, like.","startTime":"45:47","endTime":"45:57","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Exactly.","startTime":"45:58","endTime":"45:58","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"45:58","endTime":"45:59","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"45:59","endTime":"46:00","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"46:02","endTime":"46:02","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So the answer.","startTime":"46:03","endTime":"46:04","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We only had a couple questions on that.","startTime":"46:04","endTime":"46:05","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"What about getting a project manager involved?","startTime":"46:06","endTime":"46:08","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"How does that happen?","startTime":"46:08","endTime":"46:09","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is there a request for that or is there.","startTime":"46:10","endTime":"46:12","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, there's generally a request.","startTime":"46:15","endTime":"46:16","speaker_name":"Wendy Stark","speaker_id":8},{"sentence":"Unless they're already.","startTime":"46:16","endTime":"46:18","speaker_name":"Wendy Stark","speaker_id":8},{"sentence":"We have people that are assigned to teams.","startTime":"46:19","endTime":"46:22","speaker_name":"Wendy Stark","speaker_id":8},{"sentence":"Yeah, there's team alignments already.","startTime":"46:22","endTime":"46:24","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"There's team alignments.","startTime":"46:24","endTime":"46:25","speaker_name":"Wendy Stark","speaker_id":8},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"46:25","endTime":"46:25","speaker_name":"Wendy Stark","speaker_id":8},{"sentence":"So it starts out with a team alignment, and then if that PM is not available, then they come to me.","startTime":"46:25","endTime":"46:30","speaker_name":"Wendy Stark","speaker_id":8},{"sentence":"For another pm and the team alignment is around.","startTime":"46:31","endTime":"46:35","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is it centered around the customer or the salesperson?","startTime":"46:36","endTime":"46:39","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"The account manager or the customer?","startTime":"46:39","endTime":"46:42","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, yeah, it's kind of both, I would say.","startTime":"46:43","endTime":"46:45","speaker_name":"Wendy Stark","speaker_id":8},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"46:45","endTime":"46:45","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"What if you ran into a scenario where it was both?","startTime":"46:45","endTime":"46:48","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"What?","startTime":"46:51","endTime":"46:51","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"What do you mean, where it was both?","startTime":"46:51","endTime":"46:53","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So I have my order team defined on the customer record, and then I also have an order team associated with the salesperson.","startTime":"46:54","endTime":"47:00","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Salesperson creates an opportunity.","startTime":"47:00","endTime":"47:02","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"What.","startTime":"47:02","endTime":"47:03","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"What should.","startTime":"47:04","endTime":"47:04","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"What.","startTime":"47:04","endTime":"47:05","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"What team assignment should pull over, especially if they're different.","startTime":"47:05","endTime":"47:07","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So what triggers a team assignment is the account manager.","startTime":"47:08","endTime":"47:11","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So if, like, if a salesperson puts in a request and then we assign account management, Kimmy assigns Frankie on her team, then the PM would flow to Esther, and then Esther's the pm, unless Esther says she doesn't have bandwidth.","startTime":"47:12","endTime":"47:27","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Then we reassign project management.","startTime":"47:27","endTime":"47:29","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"47:31","endTime":"47:32","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So I know this is a little bit hard.","startTime":"47:34","endTime":"47:36","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I'm going to.","startTime":"47:36","endTime":"47:36","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You have to kind of abstractly think about this for a second.","startTime":"47:37","endTime":"47:39","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But.","startTime":"47:39","endTime":"47:39","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So inside of Orion, the way this works is we have this order team assignment utility.","startTime":"47:39","endTime":"47:44","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But you can kind of.","startTime":"47:45","endTime":"47:46","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You can go to the customer record and say, okay, whenever this customer has an opportunity in the future, then this salesperson, this designer, this design manager, this pm, you could.","startTime":"47:46","endTime":"47:56","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You could do all of them if you wanted to.","startTime":"47:56","endTime":"47:58","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You don't have to.","startTime":"47:58","endTime":"47:58","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We have that with some of them.","startTime":"47:58","endTime":"48:00","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Like with Wilson, we always know it's going to be the same people.","startTime":"48:00","endTime":"48:02","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"People.","startTime":"48:02","endTime":"48:02","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Or with Stanford, certain schools, we always.","startTime":"48:02","endTime":"48:05","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So right now we leave it blank if it's not.","startTime":"48:05","endTime":"48:08","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Or if we do know that customer is always going to be same people.","startTime":"48:09","endTime":"48:13","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Well, I shouldn't say.","startTime":"48:13","endTime":"48:14","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"We always fill out who the salesperson is at the customer level.","startTime":"48:14","endTime":"48:16","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay, great.","startTime":"48:17","endTime":"48:18","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And then if we do know it's.","startTime":"48:18","endTime":"48:20","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"A set team, we'll fill out the resources at the customer level so that the account manager or the PC doesn't have to go in every single time they create a new order and put all those people in there.","startTime":"48:20","endTime":"48:29","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"48:30","endTime":"48:30","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"But that doesn't.","startTime":"48:30","endTime":"48:31","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"But sometimes it does rotate.","startTime":"48:31","endTime":"48:33","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So we don't always do that.","startTime":"48:33","endTime":"48:34","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Or we'll put in.","startTime":"48:34","endTime":"48:35","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"We always know it's going to be these five people, but we don't know who these three people might be.","startTime":"48:35","endTime":"48:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Those people move in and out, so we leave those blank.","startTime":"48:40","endTime":"48:43","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So it just depends on Encore.","startTime":"48:43","endTime":"48:45","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"It's resources.","startTime":"48:45","endTime":"48:46","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"And then you can do that resource level at the customer level.","startTime":"48:46","endTime":"48:49","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"And then you can go and update.","startTime":"48:49","endTime":"48:51","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Or make edits at the project level.","startTime":"48:51","endTime":"48:53","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"48:54","endTime":"48:54","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Or the order level.","startTime":"48:54","endTime":"48:55","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"48:55","endTime":"48:55","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"48:55","endTime":"48:56","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So that's the same thing.","startTime":"48:56","endTime":"48:57","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So that works the same way.","startTime":"48:57","endTime":"48:59","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Usually it's design that's getting, you know, that we don't always know first off.","startTime":"49:00","endTime":"49:06","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"I mean, okay, we have some designers.","startTime":"49:06","endTime":"49:09","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Assigned two clients, but not always.","startTime":"49:09","endTime":"49:11","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, got it now.","startTime":"49:12","endTime":"49:15","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So that's that.","startTime":"49:15","endTime":"49:16","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So that's how Orion works.","startTime":"49:16","endTime":"49:17","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"49:17","endTime":"49:17","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Now, if we wanted to do something around the account manager where, like, if the account manager gets assigned to a opportunity, in this case, then These other people are automatically assigned.","startTime":"49:17","endTime":"49:29","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We don't currently have that now.","startTime":"49:29","endTime":"49:31","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Now it.","startTime":"49:31","endTime":"49:32","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You can say, all right, let me sign this account manager.","startTime":"49:32","endTime":"49:35","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And I know that these other people go with this account manager.","startTime":"49:35","endTime":"49:37","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I can just manually assign them.","startTime":"49:37","endTime":"49:38","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I just wanted.","startTime":"49:39","endTime":"49:40","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So if that's okay, then you have the ability to do that.","startTime":"49:40","endTime":"49:43","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, that's fine.","startTime":"49:43","endTime":"49:44","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"That's what we do today.","startTime":"49:44","endTime":"49:44","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"49:45","endTime":"49:45","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"49:46","endTime":"49:46","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"49:47","endTime":"49:47","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Kimi?","startTime":"49:47","endTime":"49:48","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"49:49","endTime":"49:50","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"If there's an associated.","startTime":"49:50","endTime":"49:51","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"And there was typically be always the same PC and then maybe pm, maybe designer.","startTime":"49:51","endTime":"49:58","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah, exactly.","startTime":"49:58","endTime":"49:59","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"But the PC is usually the one doing it.","startTime":"49:59","endTime":"50:01","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So they usually assign themselves and then they start flowing it.","startTime":"50:01","endTime":"50:05","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, okay, got it.","startTime":"50:05","endTime":"50:07","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And then.","startTime":"50:09","endTime":"50:09","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I'm sorry, did I already ask about pm?","startTime":"50:09","endTime":"50:11","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"The request for pm.","startTime":"50:12","endTime":"50:13","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So the request for pm.","startTime":"50:13","endTime":"50:15","speaker_name"